obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (72558)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72558&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Central Industrial Security Force (Amendment and`
  line `Validation) Act, 1999.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (72559)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Amendment of long title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72559&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In the Central Industrial Security Force Act, 1968 (50 of 1968)`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), for the long title, the following long title shall be substituted,`
  line `namely:–`
  line
  line `“An Act to provide for the constitution and regulation of an armed force of the Union for the`
  line `better protection and security of industrial undertakings owned by the Central Government, certain`
  line `other industrial undertakings, employees of all such undertakings and to provide technical`
  line `consultancy services to industrial establishments in the private sector and for matters connected`
  line therewith.”.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (72560)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Amendment of section 2.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72560&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In section 2 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), after clause (c), the`
  line `following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `'(ca) "industrial establishment" means an industrial undertaking or a company as defined under`
  line `section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or a firm registered under section 59 of the Indian`
  line `Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932) which is engaged in any industry, or in any trade, business or`
  line `service;'.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (72561)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Amendment of section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72561&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In section 3 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), the words “and to`
  line `perform such other duties as may be entrusted to it by the Central Government” shall be inserted at the`
  line end.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (72562)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Amendment of section 8.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72562&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `In section 8 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (i), after the word “remove”, the words “, order for compulsory retirement of ”, shall`
  line `be inserted;`
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (ii), after sub-clause (c), the following sub-clauses shall be inserted, namely:–--`
  line
  line `“(d) withholding of increment of pay with or without cumulative effect;`
  line
  line `(e) withholding of promotion;`
  line
  line `(f) censure.”.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (72563)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Amendment of section 9.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72563&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `In section 9 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (1), for the words, brackets and figure “subject to the provisions of sub-section`
  line `(3)”, the words, brackets, figures and letters “subject to the provisions of sub-section (2A), sub-`
  line `section (2B) and sub-section (3)” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) after sub-section (2), the following sub-sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“(2A) Any enrolled member of the Force aggrieved by an order passed in appeal under sub-`
  line `section (1) may, within a period of six months from the date on which the order is communicated`
  line `to him, prefer a revision petition against the order to such authority as may be prescribed and in`
  line `disposing of the revision petition, the said authority shall follow such procedure as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2B) The authority, as may be prescribed for the purpose of this sub-section, on a revision`
  line `petition preferred by an aggrieved enrolled member of the Force or suo moto, may call for, within`
  line `a prescribed period, the records of any proceeding under section 8 or sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (2A) and such authority may, after making inquiry in the prescribed manner, and`
  line `subject to the provisions of this Act, pass such order thereon as it thinks fit.”;`
  line
  line `(iii) in sub-section (3), for the words, figures and brackets “under section 8 or under sub-section`
  line `(2)”, the words, figures, brackets and letters “under section 8, sub-section (2), sub-section (2A) or`
  line `sub-section (2B)” shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (72564)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Amendment of section 10.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72564&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `In section 10 of the principal Act, after clause (e), the following`
  line `clauses shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“(f) to provide technical consultancy services relating to security of any private sector`
  line `industrial establishments under section 14A;`
  line
  line `(g) to protect and safeguard the organisations owned or funded by the Government and the`
  line `employees of such organisations as may be entrusted to him by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) any other duty which may be entrusted to him by the Central Government from time to`
  line time.”.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (72565)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Insertion of new section 14A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72565&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `After section 14 of the principal Act, the following section`
  line `shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"14A. Technical Consultancy Service to industrial establishments.--(1) Subject to any`
  line `general directions which may be issued by the Central Government, it shall be lawful for the`
  line `Director-General, on a request received from the Managing Director of an industrial`
  line `establishment in the private sector or any other person authorised by him in this behalf, to direct`
  line `the members of the Force to provide technical consultancy services relating to security, to such`
  line `industrial establishments in such manner and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The fee received under sub-section (1) shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "Managing Director", in`
  line `relation to an industrial establishment, means the person (whether called general manager,`
  line `manager, chief executive officer or a partner of a firm or by any other name) who exercises`
  line `control over the affairs of the establishment.".`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (72566)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Amendment of section 22.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72566&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `In section 22 of the principal Act, in sub-section (2),--`
  line
  line `(i) after clause (ggg), the following clauses shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“(gggg) prescribing authority under sub-section (2A) of section 9 and the procedure to be`
  line `followed by such authority in disposing of the revision petition;`
  line
  line `(ggggg) prescribing authority under sub-section (2B) of section 9, the period within which`
  line `such authority may call for the records and the manner in which such authority may make`
  line inquiry;”;
  line
  line `(ii) in clause (h), the word “and” occurring at the end shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(iii) after clause (h), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“(hh) the manner in which and the fee on payment of which the technical consultancy`
  line `services shall be provided under sub-section (1) of section 14A; and”.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (72567)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Validation of the disposal of certain revision petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145&sectionId=72567&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_23_00046_199940_1673603405145
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any judgment, decree`
  line `or order of any court to the contrary, rule 49 of the Central Industrial Security Force Rules, 1969`
  line `published with the notification of the Government of India in the Ministry of Home Affairs number S.O.`
  line `4632, dated the 12th November, 1969 shall be deemed to be, and to have always been, made under the`
  line `principal Act as amended by this Act as if the principal Act as so amended had been in force at all`
  line `material times before the commencement of this Act and accordingly the disposal of any revision petition`
  line `under the said rule 49 before the commencement of this Act or any order made or purporting to have been`
  line `made or any action or thing taken or done in or under such petition shall not be deemed to be invalid or`
  line `ever to have become invalid merely on the ground that the Central Government had no power under the`
  line `principal Act to make the said rule 49.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
